title: List of Feyenoord players
text:
<a href="Feyenoord">Feyenoord</a> is a Dutch professional <a href="association%20football">football</a> club from <a href="Rotterdam">Rotterdam</a>, that plays in the <a href="Eredivisie">Eredivisie</a>. Founded as Wilhelmina in 1908, the club changed its name in 1912 to SC Feijenoord (since 1973 Feyenoord for international reasons) and moved to <a href="De%20Kuip">De Kuip</a> in 1937. Feyenoord is one of the most successful clubs in the Netherlands, winning 15 <a href="Eredivisie">Eredivisie</a> titles, 11 <a href="KNVB%20Cup">KNVB Cup</a>s and two <a href="Johan%20Cruijff%20Schaal">Johan Cruijff Shield</a>s. The club also has won one <a href="UEFA%20Champions%20League">European Cup</a>, two <a href="UEFA%20Cup">UEFA Cup</a>s and one <a href="Intercontinental%20Cup%20%28football%29">Intercontinental Cup</a>. The club is historically one of the three clubs that have dominated the Eredivisie (first tier) of Dutch football, the others being <a href="AFC%20Ajax">Ajax</a> and <a href="PSV%20Eindhoven">PSV</a>. These three clubs have always played in the Eredivisie, since its inception in 1952, and have <a href="List%20of%20unrelegated%20association%20football%20clubs">never been relegated</a> to lower divisions.
List of players.
"Statistics correct as of 01 January 2018."
